&lt;h4&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;About the Team&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Search Discovery team owns the analytical and investigative surfaces of Cribl Search -- dashboards, notebooks, visualizations, AI-assisted investigations, and the discovery layer that helps customers get the most value out of their data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission: make it effortless for customers to explore, visualize, investigate, and act on their data through powerful, intuitive analytical experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team builds the capabilities that turn raw search results into insight: interactive dashboards, collaborative notebooks for deep analysis, rich visualizations and AI-powered investigation tools. They also own the performance and scalability of these surfaces at enterprise scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an Engineering Manager who&#39;s as excited about analytical tooling and user experience as they are about building high-performing teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and grow a senior team of engineers building Cribl&#39;s dashboards, notebooks, visualizations, investigations, and analytical discovery capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product to translate vision into execution -- surfacing ideas, shaping direction, and communicating the &quot;why&quot; to your team with clarity and energy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the team&#39;s delivery rhythm across dashboards, notebooks, visualizations, scheduled searches, AI-assisted workflows, and performance improvements that directly shape how customers interact with Cribl Search.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape technical direction alongside staff+ engineers, ensuring architectural decisions balance speed, quality, and long-term scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and develop engineers at all levels, creating shared ownership and clarity across a technically deep, senior team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a storyteller for the team -- connecting individual work to broader product vision and customer value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of engineering experience, with at least 3 years managing a team focused on user-facing product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in search, observability, analytics, or data visualization platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading senior/staff-level engineers who operate with high autonomy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong PM partnership skills -- comfortable co-creating roadmaps, translating product vision, and navigating ambiguity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with fast-paced environments where priorities shift and the team is central to the product&#39;s identity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The salary for this role is dependent on geographic location and

